headline: Walmart CFO Says They Don't Want To Raise Prices, But 'Prices Will Go Up For Consumers' Due To Upcoming Tariffs
summary: Walmart’s CFO, John David Rainey, recently said that if President-elect Donald Trump's proposed tariffs take effect, Walmart (NYSE:WMT) will need to raise prices on certain items. Speaking with CNBC, Rainey explained, "We never want to raise prices. Our model is everyday low prices. But there probably will be cases where prices will go up for consumers."
